        abstract: "In October 2024, a masked Mossad operative, “MICHAEL”, tells the American news programme <em>60 Minutes</em>: “We create a pretend world. We are a global production company—we write the screenplay, we’re the directors, we’re the producers, we’re the main actors—the world is our stage.” In pre-World War III 21st-century human life, intelligence agencies operate as the ground of reality = culture, just as in Stevan Harnad’s “symbol grounding problem”, the central nervous system grounds language—without neural and glial cellular technology, language/culture loses its informational dimension, becoming just another physical property of the universe. Every grounding operation is an instance of “non-causal metaphysical determination” (cf. Kit Fine), describing how a phenomenon X exists in virtue of a phenomenon Y, whereas shifts in ground reveal a history of grounds as discrete state transitions from one ground/state to another (from central nervous system-ground to Mossad-ground). Technology is the implementation of the grounding operation itself, both in an exoteric and esoteric sense—just as Clarke/Kubrick’s Monolith (esoteric technology) creates a reality-culture through the exoteric technology of bone as a primordial homicide weapon. Like a journey to the moon of another world, each discrete state/ground transition discloses an aspect of a deeper clandestine technics, and also why discrete state transition even takes place, or: why time can only be linear and irreversible.",
