        speaker: "Primož Krašovec",
        title: "Automation and intelligence in animals and machines",
        abstract: "My starting point will be a tension between two notions of the symbolic. In the ‘anglo’ intellectual context, symbolic means formal and logical language(s) and thought, meant to supplement or even replace the messy and unreliable natural language and everyday thinking; while in the Continental intellectual context, it mostly means the very basic feature(s) of natural language and everyday thinking, namely their propensity to abstraction as a release from lived experience(s) and concrete situation(s). In the context of AI theory and design, the first meaning of the symbolic relates to the automation of thinking as a linear, sequential procedure (symbolic AI), while the second meaning of the symbolic relates to the more recent problems, opened up by generative AI as modes of actual machine intelligence. My main thesis will be that, while important, automation is not what intelligence is but rather something that intelligence — whether living or machinic — does so rather than supplementing the symbolic as a mode of abstraction, the symbolic as a mode of automation itself has to be supplemented by a more generative and creative symbolic in order for any intelligence to function at all.",
        bio: "<strong>PRIMOŽ KRAŠOVEC</strong> is an Associate Professor at the Department of Sociology, Faculty of Arts, University of Ljubljana, where he teaches courses on epistemology, ideology, theory of technology and digital cultures. His current research areas are: antihumanities; machine intelligences; and new media cultures. In 2021 he published his first book <em>Tujost kapitala</em> (<em>Alien Capital</em>). He also co‑edits Izhodi (Exits) book series at Sophia publishing house."
